Gains and losses on crude oil swaps that are closed before the hedged production occurs are deferred until the production month originally hedged. As a result of these activities, the Company recognized net hedging losses of $1.3 million and $2.4 million for the three and six months ended June 30, 2024, respectively, and net hedging gains of $0.3 million and $0.6 million for the three and six months ended June 30, 2023, respectively, which are included in oil and gas sales in the accompanying condensed consolidated statements of operations..At June 30, 2024, the Company had no outstanding crude oil swaps